1
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:21,267
I'm just trying to do my best.

2
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:25,267
So I can you know,
get it over and done with.

3
00:00:25,333 --> 00:00:26,567
Move on with my life.

4
00:00:26,633 --> 00:00:29,800
Get out of here and go back
to my life as a designer.

5
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:31,700
That's my job,

6
00:00:31,767 --> 00:00:36,167
help you to finish your
community service quickly.

7
00:00:36,267 --> 00:00:38,733
So you can go back to the life
that you want.

8
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:40,833
Have I not made myself clear?

9
00:00:40,900 --> 00:00:44,267
I never intended to stay
here in Sorsogon.

10
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:48,000
I don't want to get involved
in that Pili nut business.

11
00:00:48,067 --> 00:00:50,733
With the same logic
that I have a life in Manila.

12
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:54,200
I'm a fashion designer there.
I have so much on my plate.

13
00:00:54,267 --> 00:00:56,000
I have no time for this.

14
00:00:56,067 --> 00:00:57,400
My life is there.

15
00:00:57,467 --> 00:01:00,033
So anything under my name,

16
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:01,500
you can do whatever you want
with it.

17
00:01:01,567 --> 00:01:05,000
Even if you feed that
to whale shark, I don't care.

18
00:01:05,067 --> 00:01:06,067
You are annoying.

19
00:01:06,133 --> 00:01:07,933
This project has nothing to do
with her.

20
00:01:08,033 --> 00:01:09,867
It's just a coincidence,

21
00:01:09,933 --> 00:01:12,233
that's where we want to go
where she's making a mess.

22
00:01:12,300 --> 00:01:14,200
I've been watching her
videos lately

23
00:01:14,267 --> 00:01:16,433
and she seems to be doing
pretty well.

24
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:20,967
She spearheaded the waste
management program in an area.

25
00:01:21,033 --> 00:01:24,467
Please, Dad, the last thing
that I want to happen there

26
00:01:24,533 --> 00:01:27,167
is to mingle
with your girlfriend.

27
00:01:27,233 --> 00:01:28,100
Hello?

28
00:01:28,167 --> 00:01:29,467
I just want to tell you

29
00:01:29,533 --> 00:01:32,000
that there will be a change in
your community service tomorrow.

30
00:01:32,067 --> 00:01:34,833
We're leaving earlier because
where we are going is far.

31
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:38,100
So prepare yourself because you
will have a long day tomorrow.

32
00:01:38,167 --> 00:01:41,200
So don't call me anymore
because I have to go to sleep.

33
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:44,133
It's already late. We have
to be early tomorrow, right?

34
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,700
So fussy!

35
00:01:45,767 --> 00:01:48,067
The two are still like cat
and dog.

36
00:01:48,133 --> 00:01:50,033
That's only in the beginning.

37
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:53,533
I knew those two very well
since they were kids.

38
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:57,467
No matter how deep the wound is
in a person's heart

39
00:01:57,533 --> 00:02:00,167
time will heal it.

40
00:02:00,233 --> 00:02:01,433
I'm so annoyed.

41
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:05,633
Someone keeps on calling me
about the schedule change.

42
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:06,800
Who?

43
00:02:06,867 --> 00:02:11,267
The one who handles
my community service.

44
00:02:11,333 --> 00:02:12,633
Well in that case,

45
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:14,733
if you're early tomorrow
I won't keep you up.

46
00:02:14,833 --> 00:02:16,800
I just called because
I wanted to inform you

47
00:02:16,867 --> 00:02:19,500
that Tiffany is going
to Sorsogon.

48
00:02:19,567 --> 00:02:21,467
She's doing a school
project there.

49
00:02:21,533 --> 00:02:24,300
I'm thinking that
this is a good opportunity

50
00:02:24,367 --> 00:02:25,967
for the two of you
to become close.

51
00:02:26,033 --> 00:02:27,367
It's your ex.

52
00:02:27,433 --> 00:02:29,400
Why is she texting at this hour?

53
00:02:29,467 --> 00:02:31,200
- What are you talking about?
- Give me the phone.

54
00:02:31,267 --> 00:02:32,400
- Oh my gosh...
- Tiffany...

55
00:02:32,467 --> 00:02:33,533
- you two are talking again?
- give me the phone.

56
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:34,900
You know what, stop the car!

57
00:02:34,967 --> 00:02:37,300
Stop the car! What's with you?

58
00:02:37,367 --> 00:02:38,700
Tiff?

59
00:02:38,767 --> 00:02:39,933
I want to be alone.

60
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:40,800
Leave!

61
00:02:40,867 --> 00:02:41,867
Fine.

62
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:46,867
Wow!

63
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:50,967
About the other day,
I'm sorry if I offended you

64
00:02:51,067 --> 00:02:53,067
when I said that I don't
have anything to do

65
00:02:53,133 --> 00:02:55,467
with the Pili nut business.

66
00:02:55,533 --> 00:02:58,433
It's just that I'm under so much
pressure with Celestial.

67
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:01,567
If she is very eager
to leave this house,

68
00:03:01,633 --> 00:03:05,700
for me, I can't wait for her
to get out of our lives.

69
00:03:05,767 --> 00:03:07,900
I don't know
why you still believe

70
00:03:07,967 --> 00:03:10,367
that this person
will have a heart.

71
00:03:10,433 --> 00:03:13,100
Sebastian, enough!

72
00:03:43,633 --> 00:03:45,533
Is there no closer community
service?

73
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:48,167
I can throw away
our neighbor's garbage.

74
00:03:48,233 --> 00:03:49,933
I mean that's still the same.

75
00:03:52,133 --> 00:03:53,300
It's taking a long time.

76
00:03:58,933 --> 00:04:01,133
I feel so exposed in this car.

77
00:04:06,133 --> 00:04:07,200
We're here.

78
00:04:13,567 --> 00:04:14,300
Do you need help?
No.

79
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,567
Is this it?

80
00:04:32,833 --> 00:04:36,967
Mother, why do we need
to come here?

81
00:04:37,033 --> 00:04:40,833
Because the most beautiful
handicrafts

82
00:04:40,900 --> 00:04:42,767
in Sorsogon are here.

83
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:48,467
Isn't it that you want to be
a fashion designer one day?

84
00:04:48,533 --> 00:04:52,533
You can get inspiration
for your fashion show.

85
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:55,667
You can also use these materials

86
00:04:55,733 --> 00:05:01,333
to make bags, belt
or even accessories.

87
00:05:01,433 --> 00:05:04,267
Why are the handicrafts
better here?

88
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:07,500
Because these are made by hands.

89
00:05:07,567 --> 00:05:08,867
Look at this.

90
00:05:10,067 --> 00:05:15,967
There's a tight knot here,
there is a loose weaving.

91
00:05:16,033 --> 00:05:20,400
There are uneven parts here.

92
00:05:20,467 --> 00:05:21,967
Like this one?

93
00:05:22,033 --> 00:05:24,567
Yes, it's not perfect.

94
00:05:24,633 --> 00:05:26,167
There are mistakes.

95
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:33,033
It's like reminding us the most
important lesson in our life.

96
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,633
Which is?

97
00:05:34,733 --> 00:05:37,967
That nobody is perfect.

98
00:05:38,033 --> 00:05:41,900
But it doesn't mean, my child,

99
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:47,700
that if we did something wrong
or do something bad

100
00:05:47,767 --> 00:05:50,967
our lives will no longer
be beautiful and colorful.

101
00:05:56,367 --> 00:05:57,333
Isn't that beautiful?

102
00:05:57,400 --> 00:06:01,933
You can put this on the side
of a shoe.

103
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,200
That's something unique.

104
00:06:03,267 --> 00:06:04,167
Even this one?

105
00:06:04,233 --> 00:06:05,967
You can maybe...

106
00:06:06,033 --> 00:06:07,700
- Maybe...
- Can we use this on a dress?

107
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:12,167
Yes, it can be used on a dress,
right?

108
00:06:12,233 --> 00:06:14,567
You have a lot to...

109
00:07:19,867 --> 00:07:21,733
Tiffany, it's your fault.

110
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,233
You have the guts to walk out,

111
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:25,567
but you didn't bring
your phone with you.

112
00:07:25,633 --> 00:07:28,667
You left it with Clau.
And you have no cash.

113
00:07:28,733 --> 00:07:31,600
Oh my gosh, how can you be
that stupid?

114
00:07:35,533 --> 00:07:37,400
That Cynthia girl is right.

115
00:07:38,767 --> 00:07:40,933
Maybe I'm really not that
bright.

116
00:07:50,967 --> 00:07:52,333
Where am I?

117
00:07:54,167 --> 00:07:55,100
I've already walked a long way.

118
00:07:55,167 --> 00:07:59,300
Maybe I'm already in Cebu
or Davao...

119
00:07:59,367 --> 00:08:00,433
or Palawan.

120
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:04,100
Oh my gosh, I need to be
in Sorsogon.

121
00:08:05,233 --> 00:08:07,400
How mad this is,
how mad this is.

122
00:08:07,467 --> 00:08:08,367
It's hopeless.

123
00:08:08,433 --> 00:08:11,467
I'm so thirsty, I'm so tired.

124
00:08:11,533 --> 00:08:12,833
Oh my God...

125
00:08:18,433 --> 00:08:19,433
Hey!

126
00:08:25,267 --> 00:08:26,233
Oh my gosh.

127
00:09:39,633 --> 00:09:45,567
There's a tight knot here,
there is a loose weaving.

128
00:09:45,633 --> 00:09:52,267
There are uneven parts here.

129
00:09:54,067 --> 00:09:56,100
There are mistakes.

130
00:09:56,167 --> 00:09:57,400
Look at this.

131
00:09:58,733 --> 00:10:04,467
It's like reminding us the most
important lesson in our life.

132
00:10:04,567 --> 00:10:06,133
Which is?

133
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,433
That nobody is perfect.

134
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:13,400
But it doesn't mean, my child,

135
00:10:13,467 --> 00:10:19,133
that if we did something wrong
or do something bad

136
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:22,500
our lives will no longer
be beautiful and colorful.

137
00:11:05,933 --> 00:11:08,500
You know you should watch where
you're going.

138
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:11,233
Miss, do you own this road?

139
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:13,967
Why? Do you own this road?

140
00:11:14,033 --> 00:11:16,100
Do you have sapak ?
(Problem with the head)

141
00:11:16,167 --> 00:11:17,833
What is sapak ?

142
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:20,300
But it sounds so negative.

143
00:11:20,367 --> 00:11:24,067
Do you think this face
has sapak, really?

144
00:11:26,433 --> 00:11:27,900
Okay.

145
00:11:27,967 --> 00:11:30,533
There's an arrogant
tourist again.

146
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:32,733
Are you from Manila?

147
00:11:33,667 --> 00:11:36,067
People from Manila are crazy.

148
00:11:38,133 --> 00:11:39,667
You know what whatever
that is...

149
00:11:39,733 --> 00:11:42,367
that negative remark, whatever.

150
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:44,900
What is your problem
if I'm from Manila?

151
00:11:44,967 --> 00:11:47,367
I'm sorry if you're just
a provincial guy.

152
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,500
- Okay.
- Wait, wait...

153
00:11:56,933 --> 00:11:58,900
Can you help me?

154
00:11:59,667 --> 00:12:02,967
Now, you're asking for help.

155
00:12:04,367 --> 00:12:06,200
Because my boyfriend
abandoned me.

156
00:12:07,767 --> 00:12:10,333
I have no cash and cellphone.

157
00:12:12,033 --> 00:12:13,433
So...

158
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:15,500
can I borrow your phone?

159
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:22,700
Thank you.

160
00:12:28,367 --> 00:12:30,400
There's no service here.

161
00:12:32,467 --> 00:12:35,833
You just said you need a
cellphone, not a signal.

162
00:12:41,033 --> 00:12:45,100
Okay, Miss, let's go
where there's a signal.

163
00:12:45,167 --> 00:12:46,600
You should come with me.

164
00:12:46,667 --> 00:12:48,800
But I have to deliver
something first.

165
00:12:51,433 --> 00:12:52,700
Let's go?

166
00:13:02,467 --> 00:13:06,767
Miss, do you a need signal
or not?

167
00:13:44,167 --> 00:13:46,033
What?

168
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,267
Sorry, Mom.

169
00:13:47,333 --> 00:13:49,333
James and I fought.

170
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:51,800
He's been a jerk.

171
00:13:51,867 --> 00:13:53,033
I'll have you picked up.

172
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:54,900
You should go home.

173
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,667
No, Mom. Please don't.

174
00:13:57,733 --> 00:14:00,367
Of course, Mom, I won't let
that jerk

175
00:14:00,433 --> 00:14:02,100
ruin my academic records.

176
00:14:02,167 --> 00:14:06,300
And even affect my work to
graduate with high honors!

177
00:14:06,367 --> 00:14:10,900
Besides, I'm with a friend.

178
00:14:10,967 --> 00:14:13,767
Actually, I'm using
his phone to call you.

179
00:14:13,833 --> 00:14:16,367
Can I talk to your friend?

180
00:14:16,433 --> 00:14:18,000
Sure.

181
00:14:19,933 --> 00:14:22,733
Can you pretend that
you're my friend?

182
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,900
All of a sudden I'm her friend.

183
00:14:32,633 --> 00:14:34,267
Hello?

184
00:14:34,333 --> 00:14:35,833
Hello?

185
00:14:36,767 --> 00:14:40,267
Yes, I'm your daughter's friend
here.

186
00:14:40,333 --> 00:14:41,733
She is safe.

187
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:43,633
Don't worry.

188
00:14:43,700 --> 00:14:45,933
What is your name?

189
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:49,833
Sebastian, you can
also call me Basti.

190
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:54,367
Basti, can you really make sure
that she's safe?

191
00:14:54,433 --> 00:14:57,200
Yes, Ma'am. She's safe here.

192
00:14:58,533 --> 00:15:02,167
Okay, can you please send me
your full name and your address?

193
00:15:02,267 --> 00:15:04,900
And I hope you don't mind
I'll call this number first

194
00:15:04,967 --> 00:15:06,600
until she gets her cellphone
back.

195
00:15:06,667 --> 00:15:09,467
And also I'll send you
her emergency fund.

196
00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:11,567
Is that okay?

197
00:15:11,633 --> 00:15:14,200
Yes, no problem.

198
00:15:14,267 --> 00:15:15,300
Thank you so much.

199
00:15:15,367 --> 00:15:17,500
Can I talk to her again?

200
00:15:17,567 --> 00:15:19,833
Okay.

201
00:15:23,933 --> 00:15:24,800
Mom?

202
00:15:24,867 --> 00:15:27,100
Tiff, I don't like this.

203
00:15:27,167 --> 00:15:28,800
Maybe we should call your dad.

204
00:15:28,867 --> 00:15:30,900
Mom, please don't.

205
00:15:30,967 --> 00:15:32,400
Please.

206
00:15:32,467 --> 00:15:35,933
He will just ask me to go
to his mistress.

207
00:15:36,033 --> 00:15:38,067
If only I don't have an
important business meeting,

208
00:15:38,133 --> 00:15:39,933
I'll go there.

209
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,433
I know, Mom. I know.

210
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:45,867
Promise, I'll call you
from time to time.

211
00:15:45,933 --> 00:15:48,967
Can you just trust me on this?
Please, Mom?

212
00:15:49,033 --> 00:15:50,267
I trust you.

213
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:54,533
Once my business engagement
is over, I'll go there.

214
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:55,833
I love you.

215
00:15:55,900 --> 00:15:57,567
I love you.

216
00:15:59,733 --> 00:16:00,667
There's a charge for that.

217
00:16:00,733 --> 00:16:02,833
It's three thousand
five hundred pesos.

218
00:16:03,067 --> 00:16:05,567
Sure, I'm rich.

219
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:07,567
Wow, she's arrogant.

220
00:16:09,267 --> 00:16:11,633
What did you say?

221
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:14,767
Nothing. I said humble...

222
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:16,333
- Humble?
- Humble.

223
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:28,467
This is a nice place.

224
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:34,733
Wait...

225
00:16:36,333 --> 00:16:38,400
only locals would know

226
00:16:38,467 --> 00:16:40,333
that there's a signal
in this area.

227
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,033
Me of all people.

228
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:44,700
I'm pure-blooded Uragon.

229
00:16:44,767 --> 00:16:48,967
I know Bicolandia and all the
areas here that has signal.

230
00:16:49,033 --> 00:16:51,033
Well...

231
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:54,167
you're exactly the right person
I'm looking for.

232
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:24,000
Well, this is a surprise.

233
00:17:24,067 --> 00:17:26,933
Is Tiffany missing again,
that's why you're here?

234
00:17:30,033 --> 00:17:33,133
Tiffany is out of town
for a school project

235
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:38,167
and I'm here because I want
to talk to you.

236
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:49,833
It's not our intention,

237
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:53,067
but this place became a
destination for women.

238
00:17:53,133 --> 00:17:58,167
Single mothers or women
who are unnoticed by society.

239
00:17:58,233 --> 00:18:01,867
What we really want
is to give jobs

240
00:18:01,933 --> 00:18:05,767
and make the people
of this community

241
00:18:05,833 --> 00:18:07,867
and the other Barangays

242
00:18:07,933 --> 00:18:13,567
that they have a place to go
if they need a livelihood.

243
00:18:13,633 --> 00:18:15,633
But more than that,

244
00:18:15,700 --> 00:18:20,600
we want to promote our tradition
in handicraft making.

245
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:22,600
That's why, we're happy
that you're here

246
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:25,833
and giving us a little
attention.

247
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:30,567
Someone who is accomplished
and a known fashion designer.

248
00:18:30,633 --> 00:18:33,067
What can I do to help you?

249
00:18:33,133 --> 00:18:37,533
Promoting us is more than
enough.

250
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:42,167
You know with the low cost
of materials from China,

251
00:18:42,233 --> 00:18:45,200
it affected us a bit.

252
00:18:45,267 --> 00:18:50,200
But if you will promote us,
maybe we can fight

253
00:18:50,267 --> 00:18:54,000
because there's a respected
fashion designer

254
00:18:54,067 --> 00:18:56,033
who believes in us.

255
00:18:59,167 --> 00:19:01,533
The truth is we know you.

256
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:04,800
We know your mother Lucinda.

257
00:19:04,867 --> 00:19:06,733
A lot of people here say

258
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:09,367
that you already forgot
where you came from.

259
00:19:09,433 --> 00:19:14,400
I told them that one day
you will go back

260
00:19:14,467 --> 00:19:17,633
and introduce us to the world.

261
00:19:19,033 --> 00:19:24,167
If you need handicrafts
or materials just tell us.

262
00:19:24,233 --> 00:19:25,933
We will give you a discount

263
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:28,500
like what we gave your mother
back then.

264
00:19:33,733 --> 00:19:34,633
Thank you.

265
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:42,900
Look at these.

266
00:19:54,133 --> 00:19:55,867
Thank you.

267
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:58,167
Basti will pay you.

268
00:19:59,433 --> 00:20:00,667
So, now what?

269
00:20:00,733 --> 00:20:03,333
You want me to be your assistant
here in Sorsogon?

270
00:20:03,433 --> 00:20:06,067
You should pay me
two thousand pesos.

271
00:20:06,133 --> 00:20:08,500
Not an assistant, Basti.

272
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:10,100
I just need someone to guide me,

273
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:13,867
so I can execute properly
my project here in Sorsogon.

274
00:20:13,933 --> 00:20:15,900
If you need a Tour Guide,

275
00:20:15,967 --> 00:20:18,367
you should go to the Tourism
Office.

276
00:20:19,733 --> 00:20:22,100
That's the problem, Basti.

277
00:20:22,167 --> 00:20:27,767
The tourism officers only show
the good side of Sorsogon.

278
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:31,700
For me, I want to know
the whole Sorsogon.

279
00:20:31,767 --> 00:20:34,400
Okay, I'll think about it.

280
00:20:36,733 --> 00:20:39,600
How much are you?

281
00:20:39,667 --> 00:20:43,100
Hey, I'm not after the money.

282
00:20:43,167 --> 00:20:45,967
Plus five thousand pesos?

283
00:20:46,033 --> 00:20:49,167
Deal, five thousand kisses
on my butt.

284
00:20:49,233 --> 00:20:50,533
You're rude.

285
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:52,667
You're rude too.

286
00:20:52,733 --> 00:20:53,800
Whatever!

287
00:20:55,433 --> 00:20:56,400
Can I borrow your phone?

288
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:57,500
I need to call Clau.

289
00:20:57,567 --> 00:20:59,133
Maybe she's coming.

290
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:03,233
I just need to check, okay.

291
00:21:13,767 --> 00:21:15,767
There's a signal here.

292
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:21,067
Tiff, are you okay?

293
00:21:21,133 --> 00:21:22,167
What happened?

294
00:21:22,233 --> 00:21:23,800
Is that James?

295
00:21:36,467 --> 00:21:38,133
So are you done being insecure?

296
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:39,367
I don't want to see your face!

297
00:21:39,433 --> 00:21:41,500
That's enough!
Bro, that's enough.

298
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:42,900
Who the hell are you?

299
00:21:44,100 --> 00:21:46,067
I'm just the one
who promised her mom

300
00:21:46,133 --> 00:21:50,100
that I won't allow a fool
like you to disrespect her.

301
00:21:50,167 --> 00:21:51,300
I'm a fool?

302
00:21:51,367 --> 00:21:52,133
Is that it?
- Do you want a fight?
- James!

303
00:21:52,867 --> 00:21:54,033
James, what's with you?

304
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:55,933
Is there a problem here?

305
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,867
I'll handle this. I'm okay.

306
00:21:57,933 --> 00:21:58,767
Tiff.

307
00:22:00,133 --> 00:22:03,067
Bro, do you have a problem?

308
00:22:03,133 --> 00:22:08,933
Maybe you have forgotten,
this is my territory.

309
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:09,967
James, let's go.

310
00:22:10,033 --> 00:22:11,067
That's enough.

311
00:22:11,133 --> 00:22:12,967
James, James!

312
00:22:25,433 --> 00:22:26,333
Thank you. I'm okay.
Okay.

313
00:22:41,333 --> 00:22:42,333
There you go.

314
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:45,333
That's right, Celeste.

315
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:51,133
You know it takes years to be
an expert in making handicrafts.

316
00:22:51,233 --> 00:22:55,100
But with you, it's natural.

317
00:22:55,167 --> 00:22:59,800
No, you are better than me.

318
00:22:59,867 --> 00:23:02,200
There should be a rhythm.

319
00:23:02,267 --> 00:23:04,233
That's important.

320
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:07,967
Not too fast, but not too slow.

321
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:43,567
Are you done?

322
00:23:43,633 --> 00:23:44,967
I want to go home.

323
00:23:45,033 --> 00:23:46,567
Why? Is there a problem?

324
00:23:46,633 --> 00:23:48,267
I just want to go home.

325
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:53,033
That concludes our business.

326
00:23:53,100 --> 00:23:54,233
With your investment,

327
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:57,400
you are now a part
of my group of companies

328
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:59,333
as a minority stake.

329
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,900
Why are you doing this?

330
00:24:00,967 --> 00:24:02,600
It's about Tonito.

331
00:24:02,667 --> 00:24:05,333
What about Tonito?

332
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:06,833
I'll make you a daily report.

333
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:08,267
You already rendered
thirty hours.

334
00:24:08,333 --> 00:24:10,267
Just record it,
so we're synchronized.

335
00:24:10,333 --> 00:24:12,133
By the way, you don't have
to pick me up tomorrow.

336
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:14,167
I'm okay, I can manage.

337
00:24:14,233 --> 00:24:15,367
Why?

338
00:24:15,433 --> 00:24:16,267
He is such a know-it-all person.

339
00:24:16,333 --> 00:24:18,433
He told me "I know
the real you".

340
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:20,367
What's that?

341
00:24:20,433 --> 00:24:21,667
Why are you laughing?

342
00:24:21,733 --> 00:24:23,967
I'm thrilled.

343
00:24:24,033 --> 00:24:25,967
Girl, why are you thrilled?

344
00:24:26,033 --> 00:24:27,233
She's very different.

345
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:28,833
She's just wearing heels and now
she thinks so highly of herself.

346
00:24:28,933 --> 00:24:30,333
She dresses up in fashion

347
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:32,133
and she's very good now
at speaking English.

348
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:34,067
But she's the same person.

349
00:24:34,133 --> 00:24:35,533
She is still an Uragon.

350
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:37,500
I even made her eat
chili ice cream.

351
00:24:37,567 --> 00:24:39,233
Does that local guy like you?

352
00:24:39,300 --> 00:24:41,133
Or maybe it's you who likes him.

353
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:44,067
Don't talk to me ever again,
you bastard!

354
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:48,900
If I were to set myself up
for another rejection,

355
00:24:48,967 --> 00:24:51,533
it must be for something
worth fighting for.

356
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:54,733
I still love Tonito
more than I will ever admit.

357
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:55,867
I'm just on a water break...

358
00:24:55,933 --> 00:24:59,433
Didn't I tell you
that you can't accept calls

359
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:01,067
while you're on duty?

360
00:25:01,133 --> 00:25:04,267
What do you mean
you don't understand?

361
00:25:05,467 --> 00:25:06,667
Something wrong?

362
00:25:06,733 --> 00:25:09,100
Do you think I still haven't
proven anything, cousin?

363
00:25:09,167 --> 00:25:10,033
What do you mean?

364
00:25:10,100 --> 00:25:12,167
Am I still that worthless
fresh graduate

365
00:25:12,233 --> 00:25:14,033
that my sister Vivian
said before?

366
00:25:14,100 --> 00:25:19,000
Celeste is just tough now,
but you can soften her heart.

367
00:25:19,067 --> 00:25:21,433
There's nothing love cannot do.

368
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:23,700
I'm really, really sorry.

369
00:25:23,767 --> 00:25:26,767
That's another 100 hours added
to your community service.

370
00:25:26,833 --> 00:25:28,067
What?
